<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="1813" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1813">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 823.00/181.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">McMillin</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-27">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 27, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your telegram of May 26. I called upon Minister for Foreign Affairs
                            to-day with the Argentine and Brazilian Ministers and informed him the
                            United States recognizes the Government of Peru. Argentina and Brazil
                            recognized at same time. Joint action was appreciated. Chile has no
                            representative here. News of proposed recognition was telegraphed from
                            Chile, appearing in this morning’s papers. /</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">McMillin</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>